  "prompt": "Why does my DIRECTV guide read \"to be announced\"?",
  "response": "If your DIRECTV guide is showing \"to be announced,\" it generally means that the programming information for that particular time slot has not yet been finalized or made available. This can happen for a few reasons:\n\n1. **Live Events:** If the programming is related to live sporting events or special broadcasts, those may not have a confirmed schedule until closer to the date.\n\n2. **Network Updates:** Sometimes, networks may not provide information in advance about their programming, especially for shows that are still in production.\n\n3. **Technical Issues:** There may be a temporary problem with the guide data being transmitted to your receiver, which can sometimes result in outdated or missing information.\n\n4. **Show Renewals or Cancellations:** If a show has been renewed or canceled recently, upcoming episodes' scheduling may be uncertain.\n\nIf the issue persists, consider resetting your receiver or checking DIRECTV's website or app for updated information. If you're still having trouble, contacting DIRECTV customer support may provide further assistance.",
